The paper focuses on the quantitative study of the relationship between visual appearance and performance of creatives in online display advertising. This involves the use of large scale data and the design of a set of visual features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is Information Retrieval (cs.IR) which deals with the retrieval of information from large-scale data. 

The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques to extract visual features from creatives, which suggests that Computer Vision (cs.CV) is another likely sub-category. 

Additionally, the paper evaluates the effectiveness of visual features for CTR prediction, ranking, and performance classification, which suggests that Multimedia (cs.MM) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) could also be relevant sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper involves the study of user response in online advertising, which could fall under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it relates to user privacy and security concerns in online advertising.
